are. They seem to reside closeby cosmic filaments and do not survive in nodes.\nBeing in a poor environment could therefore be the driver of FG formation, the\nnumber of nearby galaxies not being sufficient to compensate for the\ncannibalism of the central group galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 09:24:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 23 Apr 2020 16:04:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-22"}
