{"id":"2004.09311","submitter":"Stephen Teitel","authors":"Peter Olsson and S. Teitel","title":"Dynamic length scales in athermal, shear-driven, jamming of frictionless\n  disks in two dimensions","comments":"12 pages, 14 figures; updated to published version","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. E 102, 042906 (2020)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevE.102.042906","report-no":null,"categories":"cond-mat.soft","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We carry our numerical simulations of athermally sheared, bidisperse,\nfrictionless disks in two dimensions. From an appropriately defined velocity\ncorrelation function, we determine that there are two diverging length scales,\n$\\xi$ and $\\ell$, as the jamming transition is approached. We analyze our\nresults using a critical scaling ansatz for the correlation function, and argue\nthat the more divergent length $\\ell$ is a consequence of a dangerous\nirrelevant scaling variable, and that it is $\\xi$ which is the correlation\nlength that determines the divergence of the system viscosity as jamming is\napproached from below in the liquid phase. We find that $\\xi\\sim\n(\\phi_J-\\phi)^{-\\nu}$ diverges with the critical exponent $\\nu=1$. We provide\nevidence that $\\xi$ measures the length scale of fluctuations in the rotation\nof the particle velocity field, while $\\ell$ measures the length scale of\nfluctuations in the divergence of the velocity field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 14:01:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 22 Oct 2020 08:21:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-23"}
