, and the resulting plasmon lifetime first decreases from infinity\nand then increases as q grows from 0 toward the electron-hole continuum. A\nstatic charge-density wave is found for r$_s$ $>$ 69, and shown to be\nassociated with softening of the plasmon mode. The exchange-only version of our\nstatic kernel confirms Overhauser's 1968 prediction that correlation enhances\nthe charge-density wave.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 14:14:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-07-01"}
